The Vice President visited Nellis Air Force Base in Nevada and gave a speech to thank the military personnel for their service. He brought greetings from President Donald Trump and expressed the administration's commitment to supporting the armed forces and veterans. He highlighted the investments made in national defense, including the development of new aircraft and equipment, and the largest pay raise for the military in nearly 10 years. The Vice President also praised Senator Dean Heller for his support of veterans and mentioned the improvements made in veterans programs, such as the VA appeals process and the Veterans Choice program. He concluded by expressing his pride and gratitude for the men and women serving at Nellis Air Force Base.